00:03:18.386 --> 00:03:21.366 A:middle
the language of your app, your

00:03:21.536 --> 00:03:23.106 A:middle
app will be relaunched in the

00:03:23.106 --> 00:03:23.976 A:middle
target language.

00:03:24.826 --> 00:03:25.976 A:middle
Now, to make this language

00:03:25.976 --> 00:03:27.616 A:middle
change a seamless experience for

00:03:27.616 --> 00:03:29.436 A:middle
the user, we recommend you adapt

00:03:29.726 --> 00:03:31.946 A:middle
state restoration APIs.

00:03:32.636 --> 00:03:34.526 A:middle
In iOS 13, there are some new

00:03:34.526 --> 00:03:36.926 A:middle
state restoration APIs with

00:03:36.926 --> 00:03:38.136 A:middle
NSUserActivity.

00:03:38.546 --> 00:03:39.596 A:middle
To learn more about how you can

00:03:39.596 --> 00:03:40.906 A:middle
use them, you can check out this

00:03:40.906 --> 00:03:41.856 A:middle
talk on Friday.

00:03:42.586 --> 00:03:45.796 A:middle
And, finally, it's important

00:03:45.796 --> 00:03:47.076 A:middle
that all of your content is

00:03:47.076 --> 00:03:48.596 A:middle
shown consistently in one

00:03:48.596 --> 00:03:49.736 A:middle
language throughout your app.

00:03:50.636 --> 00:03:51.966 A:middle
If you're doing some custom or

00:03:52.056 --> 00:03:53.446 A:middle
server-side resource loading,

00:03:53.816 --> 00:03:55.386 A:middle
there are handful of APIs that

00:03:55.386 --> 00:03:56.556 A:middle
might be useful for you to

00:03:56.556 --> 00:03:57.606 A:middle
determine which language to

00:03:57.606 --> 00:03:58.676 A:middle
request that content here.

00:03:59.766 --> 00:04:00.856 A:middle
Let's go over a few of them.

00:03:59.766 --> 00:04:00.856 A:middle
Let's go over a few of them.

00:04:02.406 --> 00:04:04.286 A:middle
Locale APIs are useful for

00:04:04.286 --> 00:04:06.106 A:middle
fetching the user's Language and

00:04:06.106 --> 00:04:07.016 A:middle
Region preferences.

00:04:07.826 --> 00:04:09.536 A:middle
Locale that preferred languages

00:04:09.776 --> 00:04:11.536 A:middle
returns a list of languages in

00:04:11.536 --> 00:04:12.776 A:middle
order of user preference.

00:04:13.636 --> 00:04:15.546 A:middle
Now, this list might be useful

00:04:15.546 --> 00:04:18.375 A:middle
to you if maybe you're building

00:04:18.375 --> 00:04:19.315 A:middle
an app that needs to handle

00:04:19.315 --> 00:04:21.536 A:middle
multilingual content, and you

00:04:21.536 --> 00:04:22.716 A:middle
need to fetch resources such as

00:04:22.786 --> 00:04:24.476 A:middle
font for all of the user's

00:04:24.476 --> 00:04:24.846 A:middle
languages.

00:04:24.846 --> 00:04:27.876 A:middle
And one thing to know is that

00:04:28.136 --> 00:04:29.396 A:middle
locale, that preferred languages

00:04:29.396 --> 00:04:32.206 A:middle
will return the language list,

00:04:32.296 --> 00:04:33.396 A:middle
that user's preferred languages,

00:04:33.436 --> 00:04:35.016 A:middle
regardless of the languages your

00:04:35.016 --> 00:04:36.356 A:middle
application bundle supports.

00:04:36.816 --> 00:04:37.996 A:middle
So it's not useful for getting

00:04:37.996 --> 00:04:39.196 A:middle
the current running application

00:04:39.196 --> 00:04:39.626 A:middle
language.

00:04:40.826 --> 00:04:41.746 A:middle
To get the current running

00:04:41.746 --> 00:04:44.066 A:middle
