00:04:55.716 --> 00:04:57.096 A:middle
languages that your application

00:04:57.096 --> 00:04:58.896 A:middle
bundle supports and returns a

00:04:58.896 --> 00:05:00.096 A:middle
list of languages your

00:04:58.896 --> 00:05:00.096 A:middle
list of languages your

00:05:00.096 --> 00:05:01.766 A:middle
application Bundle supports in

00:05:01.766 --> 00:05:02.806 A:middle
order of user preference.

00:05:04.386 --> 00:05:05.486 A:middle
Now, if you have an external

00:05:05.486 --> 00:05:06.526 A:middle
list, say if you're loading some

00:05:06.526 --> 00:05:08.226 A:middle
remote content from a server and

00:05:08.226 --> 00:05:09.166 A:middle
your server has a different

00:05:09.166 --> 00:05:10.646 A:middle
setup supported languages, you

00:05:10.646 --> 00:05:11.786 A:middle
can use the class method

00:05:11.866 --> 00:05:13.466 A:middle
Bundle.preferredLocalizations

00:05:13.536 --> 00:05:13.806 A:middle
from.

00:05:14.276 --> 00:05:15.706 A:middle
And this will also consider that

00:05:15.766 --> 00:05:17.866 A:middle
third language from your server.

