00:20:31.046 --> 00:20:32.216 A:middle
Now, let's take a look at how

00:20:32.216 --> 00:20:33.926 A:middle
you can take advantage of UI

00:20:33.926 --> 00:20:35.086 A:middle
testing for localization.

00:20:36.466 --> 00:20:38.246 A:middle
Testing is a significant part of

00:20:38.246 --> 00:20:39.226 A:middle
any development cycle.

00:20:39.716 --> 00:20:41.976 A:middle
It takes time and resources but

00:20:41.976 --> 00:20:43.066 A:middle
it's very important to help

00:20:43.096 --> 00:20:44.586 A:middle
catch regressions as you add new

00:20:44.586 --> 00:20:46.836 A:middle
features and detect bugs before

00:20:46.836 --> 00:20:48.316 A:middle
you release your product to your

00:20:48.316 --> 00:20:48.726 A:middle
customers.

00:20:51.376 --> 00:20:52.826 A:middle
If your app support more than

00:20:52.826 --> 00:20:54.496 A:middle
one language you will have to

00:20:54.496 --> 00:20:55.716 A:middle
test full language specific

00:20:55.716 --> 00:20:56.036 A:middle
issues.

00:20:56.866 --> 00:21:00.586 A:middle
Clip strings, truncated content,

00:20:56.866 --> 00:21:00.586 A:middle
Clip strings, truncated content,

00:21:01.396 --> 00:21:04.186 A:middle
overlapping layouts or even

00:21:04.186 --> 00:21:05.586 A:middle
issues specific to right-to-left

00:21:05.586 --> 00:21:06.866 A:middle
languages such as Hebrew,

00:21:06.866 --> 00:21:07.186 A:middle
Arabic.

00:21:09.696 --> 00:21:12.106 A:middle
Now, if you want to test for

00:21:12.106 --> 00:21:15.386 A:middle
every device you support, in

00:21:15.586 --> 00:21:18.566 A:middle
every language you support, your

00:21:18.566 --> 00:21:19.956 A:middle
test metrics can repeat and

00:21:19.956 --> 00:21:20.256 A:middle
explore.

00:21:21.836 --> 00:21:23.636 A:middle
You can easily end up with

00:21:23.726 --> 00:21:24.616 A:middle
thousands of different

00:21:24.616 --> 00:21:24.956 A:middle
scenarios.

00:21:26.236 --> 00:21:27.166 A:middle
And that will make it really

00:21:27.166 --> 00:21:28.586 A:middle
difficult for your testers to

00:21:28.586 --> 00:21:29.626 A:middle
cover all these scenarios

00:21:29.626 --> 00:21:29.936 A:middle
manually.

00:21:30.446 --> 00:21:32.136 A:middle
So, it's even more important to

00:21:32.136 --> 00:21:34.016 A:middle
include test in your project to

00:21:34.016 --> 00:21:35.146 A:middle
help produce manual work load

00:21:35.206 --> 00:21:36.496 A:middle
for your QA.

00:21:37.736 --> 00:21:40.936 A:middle
In Xcode 11, we made it easier

00:21:40.936 --> 00:21:42.686 A:middle
for you to cover all of this

00:21:42.686 --> 00:21:44.196 A:middle
test automatically with test

00:21:44.706 --> 00:21:44.976 A:middle
plans.

00:21:45.516 --> 00:21:49.206 A:middle
[ Applause ]

00:21:49.706 --> 00:21:51.316 A:middle
Test plan is a very easy way to

00:21:51.316 --> 00:21:53.126 A:middle
run the same tests multiple

00:21:53.126 --> 00:21:54.546 A:middle
times using different

00:21:54.546 --> 00:21:55.176 A:middle
configurations.

00:21:56.386 --> 00:21:57.456 A:middle
I'm not going to go too much

00:21:57.456 --> 00:21:58.616 A:middle
into details about test plans

00:21:58.616 --> 00:21:58.866 A:middle
today.

00:21:58.956 --> 00:22:00.576 A:middle
So please check out the Testing

