00:22:27.806 --> 00:22:29.376 A:middle
those screenshots, because

00:22:29.376 --> 00:22:30.566 A:middle
they're not only good for

00:22:31.496 --> 00:22:31.686 A:middle
testing.

00:22:33.506 --> 00:22:36.316 A:middle
First, let's see how we can make

00:22:36.316 --> 00:22:37.876 A:middle
sure that your test can work in

00:22:37.876 --> 00:22:38.916 A:middle
every language you run them in.

00:22:40.416 --> 00:22:43.026 A:middle
To do so, you should rely on

00:22:43.026 --> 00:22:44.236 A:middle
Accessibility Identifiers.

00:22:45.536 --> 00:22:47.056 A:middle
These identifiers are unique,

00:22:47.646 --> 00:22:49.856 A:middle
stable, and we'll guarantee that

00:22:49.856 --> 00:22:51.236 A:middle
your test can run in any

00:22:51.236 --> 00:22:51.626 A:middle
language.

00:22:53.626 --> 00:22:55.696 A:middle
You can easily set them up,

00:22:55.766 --> 00:22:56.776 A:middle
setting the property of the same

00:22:56.776 --> 00:22:59.796 A:middle
name in code or if you're using

00:22:59.866 --> 00:23:01.246 A:middle
interface Builder to create your

00:22:59.866 --> 00:23:01.246 A:middle
interface Builder to create your

00:23:01.246 --> 00:23:03.626 A:middle
UI element, you can define them

00:23:03.626 --> 00:23:04.796 A:middle
right there in the Identity

00:23:04.796 --> 00:23:08.966 A:middle
Inspector, and that's all it

00:23:08.966 --> 00:23:09.336 A:middle
takes.

00:23:09.696 --> 00:23:10.626 A:middle
So, now, that your test are

00:23:10.626 --> 00:23:12.656 A:middle
