up to capture Localized

00:23:58.696 --> 00:24:00.336 A:middle
Screenshots, let's see what we

00:23:58.696 --> 00:24:00.336 A:middle
Screenshots, let's see what we

00:24:00.336 --> 00:24:00.886 A:middle
can do with them.

00:24:01.726 --> 00:24:02.526 A:middle
They're actually a great

00:24:02.566 --> 00:24:03.396 A:middle
marketing resource.

00:24:04.026 --> 00:24:05.286 A:middle
You can pass them along to your

00:24:05.286 --> 00:24:07.516 A:middle
marketing team or even upload

00:24:07.516 --> 00:24:08.966 A:middle
them to the App Store to

00:24:09.036 --> 00:24:11.396 A:middle
showcase your latest design.

00:24:11.556 --> 00:24:12.626 A:middle
You can use them in your

00:24:12.626 --> 00:24:14.096 A:middle
documentation or in your

00:24:14.096 --> 00:24:14.526 A:middle
tutorials.

00:24:17.156 --> 00:24:19.706 A:middle
But more importantly they can

00:24:19.706 --> 00:24:21.296 A:middle
help your localizers get the

00:24:21.296 --> 00:24:23.106 A:middle
context they need to provide you

00:24:23.106 --> 00:24:24.696 A:middle
with high quality localization.

00:24:25.326 --> 00:24:27.656 A:middle
Let's take a quick example.

00:24:28.446 --> 00:24:31.596 A:middle
A simple word like Start in

00:24:31.596 --> 00:24:33.616 A:middle
English could either be a verb

00:24:33.886 --> 00:24:36.426 A:middle
meaning to begin or it could be

00:24:36.426 --> 00:24:37.736 A:middle
a noun and referred to the

00:24:37.736 --> 00:24:38.526 A:middle
beginning of an event.

00:24:39.656 --> 00:24:41.066 A:middle
While this difference might seem

00:24:41.066 --> 00:24:42.546 A:middle
really subtle in English, it can

00:24:42.546 --> 00:24:43.676 A:middle
lead to widely different

00:24:43.676 --> 00:24:44.586 A:middle
localizations in other

00:24:44.586 --> 00:24:45.226 A:middle
languages.

00:24:46.716 --> 00:24:48.586 A:middle
Here, we can see it's a noun

00:24:48.586 --> 00:24:49.526 A:middle
because it's labeling the

00:24:49.596 --> 00:24:50.886 A:middle
starting date.

00:24:51.936 --> 00:24:53.776 A:middle
Giving this visual context to

00:24:53.776 --> 00:24:55.536 A:middle
your localizers we'll alleviate

00:24:55.536 --> 00:24:57.096 A:middle
the ambiguity and make sure that

00:24:57.136 --> 00:24:58.146 A:middle
you get the most accurate

00:24:58.146 --> 00:24:58.756 A:middle
localization.

00:25:01.056 --> 00:25:03.706 A:middle
Last year, we introduced the

00:25:03.706 --> 00:25:04.836 A:middle
Xcode Localization Catalog.

00:25:06.466 --> 00:25:08.226 A:middle
It's a very common way to handle

00:25:08.226 --> 00:25:10.446 A:middle
localizing both strings and

00:25:10.446 --> 00:25:12.786 A:middle
non-string based resources all

00:25:12.786 --> 00:25:14.556 A:middle
in one place.

00:25:15.716 --> 00:25:17.696 A:middle
In it we included the Notes

00:25:17.696 --> 00:25:19.546 A:middle
directory, specifically for you

00:25:19.546 --> 00:25:20.636 A:middle
to include contextual

00:25:20.636 --> 00:25:22.346 A:middle
information such as screenshots

00:25:22.606 --> 00:25:25.206 A:middle
for your localizers.

00:25:26.066 --> 00:25:28.366 A:middle
This year, I'm very happy to say

00:25:28.576 --> 00:25:29.646 A:middle
that we are automatically

00:25:29.646 --> 00:25:30.906 A:middle
including these screenshots for

00:25:30.906 --> 00:25:32.346 A:middle
you in the Xcode Localization

00:25:32.346 --> 00:25:32.976 A:middle
Catalog catalog.

00:25:33.516 --> 00:25:37.836 A:middle
[ Applause ]

00:25:38.336 --> 00:25:40.516 A:middle
And all it takes in one-- is one

